cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on robotic automation and learning contact skills for assembly tasks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses a Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) network for learning the contact skills from human demonstrations.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper involves developing an algorithm for programming force-sensitive assembly tasks in a robot-independent way.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions using simulation environments for extracting and learning the contact skills.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper involves solving the inverse kinematics problem using forward dynamics computation.
